        <hl1>On the Grand Day for Bush, American Voices</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Defense Debate Begins'' (editorial, Aug. 2):</p>
        <p>You chide George W. Bush for sticking to a defense plan that includes building a missile defense system. Do you have any alternative suggestions besides good diplomacy and eternal optimism to deal with the looming threat posed by rogue nations like North Korea and Iraq?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Defense Debate Begins'' (editorial, Aug. 2):</p>
        <p>You chide George W. Bush for sticking to a defense plan that includes building a missile defense system. Do you have any alternative suggestions besides good diplomacy and eternal optimism to deal with the looming threat posed by rogue nations like North Korea and Iraq?</p>
        <p>Even if it takes 25 to 50 years to carry out a missile defense plan that is adequate, it would be well worth it, if our planet survives that long.</p>
        <p>EDWARD WRONKA  Morris Plains, N.J., Aug. 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
